snippet.textDisplay:
Better hope LastPass doesn´t get hacked or 100% of everything is compromised. Instead of using the same password everywhere. Store all your passwords and usernames in one place behind 1 password. Now the Hackers only need to hack LastPass instead of making sure you actually are using the same password in each place and guessing if you even have an account there. You are actually decreasing security. Since before you may actually have used several email addresses, 3 or 4 passwords and multiple usernames. Now they need 1 email and 1 password to get all your accounts.


Password managers are a terrible idea. Best passwords are long phrases that are easy to remember but hard to guess. Then use several email addresses and usernames so that even if a password you use more than once get´s figured out they don´t have the email address you used on another service.

I have better solution!!! Just have a Gaming room where you can play games, have Living room on the other side of the wall, drill a hole trough, pull trough some cables you need and plug it in your TV.
If you wanna game in Living room with a controller then you can also buy some wireless thingies you can put under TV so they pick up signal from gamepad and transfer it to the PC on the other side of the wall... This is basically the same but cheaper solution... I personally have a Gaming room where I spend most of my time and if I leave then I have no time to play games... Amazing video but pointless because not everyone have 30K for HW nobody needs... What would be really cool is having a PC at home but trough internet connect your pocket console like Nintendo Switch to it trough internet and play games from your PC... I know it will have connection issues and latency problems but this is the way we are going to play games... I know its not just me but many people probably agree with me about playing games outside of the Gaming room... If Iam in the living room then obviously I left gaming room not to play games in the living room but because i have some other business there than play games and if I want to play agane I go back to gaming room where nobody can disturb me... Not even my wife, kid or cats xD (yes I have 2 cats but only one of them likes me Q_Q ).

Linus Tech tips: I have a recommendation for your cable management and safety problem with breakage from possible animals and general wear and tear and breaking....
I to have extreme amount of wires for all my set-ups and what I'm doing now is making and using PVC pipes with a slit down the centre for potential access and in some areas double pie page one over the other I install all my wires through these pipes they are not visible any more wires it looks cleaner it can have a steampunk design and with the right back-plains end connectors you can literally move anything around plus having 12 12 Port right or left angle power bars running through a surge protector you can make things look clean neat tidy and you don't have to worry about accidentally ripping apart a wire or having rodents or other things eat the wires and you can make almost any custom design layout you want give it a try maybe do a video on

11- IR repeater ovip

snippet.textDisplay: usb 3.x would get overloaded on such a system easier than you'd think because of the way device/end points are counted you tend to have less port support than you'd think, its why they make the more expensive pci-e usb cards with multiple root hub controllers, don't be fooled by multiple ports, they are usually just the first hub connected to a single controller.  Its not 127 devices, its closer to 30 last i checked, a couple usb mice/drives/soundcards/headsets over multiple systems and you will be out of usb resources which is always fun, plug something in and nothing happens.
